<subSubSection id="15DE5FE0FF8FEF4CFF42FD07FDFBFCE4" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF8FEF4CFF42FD07FCD3FC80" blockId="39.[151,1437,617,861]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF8FEF4CFF42FD07FEE7FD74" bold="true" box="[199,338,690,716]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Comments:</emphasis>
Here we recorded for the first time the male of the species. Males present a subgenital plate common to the species of the genus, rounded, without a median keel, with posterior processes relatively long and with many bristles. The cerci are long, pilose, a little longer than the subgenital plate, with a straight and large base, with a curved apex, similar to a spatula, and with a little apical spine.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF8FEF4CFF42FCF7FDFBFCE4" blockId="39.[151,1437,617,861]" box="[199,590,834,861]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
